# `ros2_ws` System Guide

This document describes the active Go2 system as it is actually used now, including the pieces that live outside this workspace.

## Active Roots

Top-level directories that matter for the current robot and simulation workflows:

- [`/home/ming/ros2_ws`](/home/ming/ros2_ws)
  - Main ROS 2 workspace for the bridge, navigation, custom nodes, and active launch files.
- [`/home/ming/unitree_ros2`](/home/ming/unitree_ros2)
  - Official Unitree ROS 2 environment used for the real robot DDS connection.
- [`/home/ming/unitree_sdk2`](/home/ming/unitree_sdk2)
  - Kept as the main Unitree SDK tree used by the official stack and its build environment.
- [`/home/ming/rl_sar`](/home/ming/rl_sar)
  - External RL-sar MuJoCo simulator and policy/runtime stack used for the active simulation workflow.

Older roots that were intentionally archived and are no longer part of the intended workflow:

- [`/home/ming/archive_obsolete_2026-03-17`](/home/ming/archive_obsolete_2026-03-17)
  - contains `cyclonedds`, `cyclonedds-python`, `go2_python_sdk`, `go2_robot_upstream`, `unitree_mujoco`, `unitree_mujoco_venv`, `unitree_rl_gym`, `unitree_rl_lab`, and `unitree_sdk2_python`

## Environment Entry Points

Supported workflows are exposed through shell helpers in [`~/.bashrc`](~/.bashrc).

Base environment functions:

- `robot_mode`
  - sources:
    - [`/home/ming/unitree_ros2/setup_go2_humble.sh`](/home/ming/unitree_ros2/setup_go2_humble.sh)
    - `/home/ming/unitree_ros2/example/install/setup.bash`
    - `/home/ming/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash`
  - intended for the real robot
- `sim_mode`
  - uses CycloneDDS and only sources `/home/ming/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash`
  - mostly a helper for generic sim testing

Current supported command helpers:

- `go2_bridge`
  - real robot bridge only
- `go2_nav_robot`
  - real robot mapping / live-SLAM Nav2
- `go2_nav_robot_localize`
  - real robot localization on a saved map
- `go2_rlsar_sim`
  - RL-sar simulator bridge only
- `go2_rlsar_test`
  - RL-sar bridge smoke test
- `go2_nav_rlsar`
  - RL-sar mapping / live-SLAM Nav2
- `go2_nav_rlsar_localize`
  - RL-sar localization on a saved map
- `go2_nav_rlsar_localize_mppi`
  - explicit RL-sar localization using the MPPI config
- `go2_nav_rlsar_localize_dwb`
  - explicit RL-sar localization using the older DWB config
- `go2_nav_rlsar_test`
  - RL-sar Nav2 smoke test
- `go2_rlsar_reset`
  - calls the RL-sar reset ROS service from any terminal

## Real Robot Stack

The real robot path depends on all of the following:

1. [`/home/ming/unitree_ros2`](/home/ming/unitree_ros2)
   - provides the official Unitree ROS 2 setup and DDS connection scripts
   - the important setup file is [`setup_go2_humble.sh`](/home/ming/unitree_ros2/setup_go2_humble.sh)
2. [`/home/ming/unitree_sdk2`](/home/ming/unitree_sdk2)
   - provides the Unitree SDK used by the official environment
3. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge)
   - converts the official Unitree-side topics into standard ROS topics used by the rest of the system
4. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation)
   - launches SLAM, localization, Nav2, and helper nodes
5. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_robot_sdk`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_robot_sdk)
   - still supplies important robot-side Nav2 and SLAM parameter files used by the active robot launches
6. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/unitree_go2/unitree_go2_description`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/unitree_go2/unitree_go2_description)
   - provides the URDF/xacro used for robot visualization and TF structure

Normal real robot launches:

- `go2_bridge`
  - starts [`go2_unitree_bridge.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/launch/go2_unitree_bridge.launch.py)
  - exposes `/odom`, `/imu/data`, `/joint_states`, `/tf`, `/robot_description`, and Foxglove topics
- `go2_nav_robot`
  - starts [`go2_nav_robot.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_robot.launch.py)
  - intended for mapping with live SLAM
- `go2_nav_robot_localize map:=...`
  - starts [`go2_nav_robot_localization.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_robot_localization.launch.py)
  - intended for localization and Nav2 on a saved map

## RL-sar Simulation Stack

The RL-sar path depends on all of the following:

1. [`/home/ming/rl_sar`](/home/ming/rl_sar)
   - external simulator root
   - contains the MuJoCo-based RL-sar runtime, policies, robot descriptions, and the `rl_sim_mujoco` binary
2. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge)
   - starts the ROS integration around RL-sar
   - publishes synthetic `/scan`, TF, robot description, and obstacle markers for the active scene
3. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation)
   - launches mapping, localization, Nav2, target-following, goal tolerance markers, and sim fall recovery
4. [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/unitree_go2/unitree_go2_description`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/unitree_go2/unitree_go2_description)
   - provides the robot model used by visualization and `robot_state_publisher`

Normal RL-sar launches:

- `go2_rlsar_sim`
  - starts [`go2_rlsar_sim.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/launch/go2_rlsar_sim.launch.py)
  - launches the RL-sar bridge, scan node, Foxglove bridge, robot state publisher, robot description publisher, and obstacle markers
- `go2_nav_rlsar`
  - starts [`go2_nav_rlsar.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_rlsar.launch.py)
  - intended for map creation with live SLAM
- `go2_nav_rlsar_localize map:=...`
  - starts [`go2_nav_rlsar_localization.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_rlsar_localization.launch.py)
  - intended for localization and Nav2 on a saved static map

Important RL-sar-specific behavior that has been added:

- a ROS reset service `/go2_rlsar_reset`
- a shell helper `go2_rlsar_reset`
- auto initial-pose publication on localization bringup
- goal publication from `/target_location`
- goal-tolerance visualization on `/target_location_tolerance`
- sim fall recovery that can reset and republish the last target

## Main Active Packages Inside `ros2_ws`

### `src/go2_unitree_bridge`

Purpose:

- active bridge layer for both the real robot and the RL-sar simulator

Main responsibilities:

- real robot:
  - bridge official Unitree ROS 2 topics into a standard ROS nav stack shape
- RL-sar sim:
  - launch RL-sar support nodes
  - publish synthetic `/scan`
  - publish scene obstacle markers
  - expose Foxglove topics and robot description

Important files:

- [`launch/go2_unitree_bridge.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/launch/go2_unitree_bridge.launch.py)
- [`launch/go2_rlsar_sim.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/launch/go2_rlsar_sim.launch.py)
- [`go2_unitree_bridge/bridge_node.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/go2_unitree_bridge/bridge_node.py)
- [`go2_unitree_bridge/rlsar_scan_node.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/go2_unitree_bridge/rlsar_scan_node.py)
- [`go2_unitree_bridge/rlsar_obstacle_markers.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_unitree_bridge/go2_unitree_bridge/rlsar_obstacle_markers.py)

Status:

- active and required

### `src/go2_navigation`

Purpose:

- active high-level navigation layer for both robot and simulator

Main responsibilities:

- mapping launches
- localization launches
- Nav2 configuration
- target goal forwarding from `/target_location`
- default initial-pose publication
- tolerance-marker visualization
- RL-sar sim fall recovery

Important files:

- launches:
  - [`go2_nav_robot.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_robot.launch.py)
  - [`go2_nav_robot_localization.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_robot_localization.launch.py)
  - [`go2_nav_rlsar.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_rlsar.launch.py)
  - [`go2_nav_rlsar_localization.launch.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/launch/go2_nav_rlsar_localization.launch.py)
- nodes:
  - [`location_subscriber.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/go2_navigation/location_subscriber.py)
  - [`initial_pose_publisher.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/go2_navigation/initial_pose_publisher.py)
  - [`goal_tolerance_marker.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/go2_navigation/goal_tolerance_marker.py)
  - [`sim_fall_recovery.py`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/go2_navigation/sim_fall_recovery.py)
- configs:
  - [`rlsar_nav2_localization.yaml`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/config/rlsar_nav2_localization.yaml)
  - [`rlsar_nav2_localization_mppi.yaml`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/config/rlsar_nav2_localization_mppi.yaml)
  - [`robot_nav2_localization.yaml`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/config/robot_nav2_localization.yaml)

Status:

- active and required

### `src/go2_robot_sdk`

Purpose:

- older Go2 ROS package tree that still contributes important configs to the active robot path

What is still actively used:

- robot-side Nav2 parameters
- SLAM parameters
- some lidar and pointcloud configuration used by the robot navigation path

What is not part of the main supported path anymore:

- older presentation and experimental launch paths
- older direct SDK bridging ideas that were superseded by `go2_unitree_bridge`

Status:

- partially active

### `src/go2_interfaces`

Purpose:

- custom message definitions used by the active stack

Status:

- active dependency

### `src/unitree_go2`

Purpose:

- mixed legacy subtree, but still important because the description package is active

What is still actively used:

- [`unitree_go2_description`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/unitree_go2/unitree_go2_description)
  - URDF/xacro for visualization and TF
  - Foxglove-compatible robot description path

What is mostly legacy:

- `champ`
- `champ_base`
- `champ_msgs`
- the old Gazebo sim path under `unitree_go2_sim`

There is still local modification in this tree, so treat it as shared state, not dead code.

Status:

- `unitree_go2_description` is active
- most of the rest is legacy

## Maps and Navigation Modes

Saved maps live in:

- [`/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/maps`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/maps)

Current RL-sar map files:

- [`rlsar_scene.yaml`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/maps/rlsar_scene.yaml)
- [`rlsar_scene.pgm`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/maps/rlsar_scene.pgm)
- [`rlsar_scene.pre_obstacles.pgm`](/home/ming/ros2_ws/src/go2_navigation/maps/rlsar_scene.pre_obstacles.pgm)

Recommended mental model:

- mapping launches:
  - use SLAM and create or update a map
- localization launches:
  - load a saved static map and run Nav2 on top of it

## Foxglove Notes

The active launches expose Foxglove-compatible topics for:

- `/map`
- `/scan`
- `/tf`
- `/tf_static`
- `/odom`
- `/robot_description`
- `/obstacle_markers`
- `/target_location_tolerance`

The robot model path has been adjusted so that:

- mesh-based visuals can be used when Foxglove accepts them
- a simpler fallback path exists for compatibility
- the old Velodyne subtree is disabled by default in the active flows

